  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Shelter , NFI and WASH assistance for IDPs and Host Community in inaccessible villages of Khugiani and Surkhroad district of Nangrahar province.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will provide assistance as follows:

I: Under HRP 2018: ESNFI Outcome 1.5 - IDP, returnee, refugee and non-displaced conflict affected women, men and children of all ages are protected from the elements and exposure through safe emergency shelter which reduces the likelihood of disease and death and SO1: Save lives in the areas of highest need
A:- In Khugiani district of Nangrahar province.(Kaga Bazar, Hakim Abad, Khair Mena, Banda, Sara Qala, Khawaran, Murdar Dand, Chamtala)

1:- 250 families will receive cash assistance for upgrading their shelters damaged during the war between AGE in Khugiani district.
2:- 400 families will receive cash for NFI assistance.
3:- 320 families will receive house rent for 3 months as emergency shelter assistance.

B:- In Surkhrod district of Nangrahar province. (Tatang, Banda Mirlamje, Bala Bagh Daryab, Bar Kako Khil, Koz Sultanpor, Fati Abad,Bagh Bani, Bar kakrak, koz kakrak, Bala Bagh and Bagrami villages)

1:- 200 recent IDP families will receive cash for NFI assistance.
3:- 300 families will receive house rent for 3 months as emergency shelter assistance.

II: Under HRP 2018 : WASH Outcome 1.4 - WASH related communicable diseases are reduced
among IDP, returnee, refugee and non-displaced conflict-affected women, men and children of all ages through timely and adequate WASH assistance, WASH Cluster objective 1: Ensure that the affected population have access to sufficient safe water, sanitation and means of hygiene and SO1: Save lives in the areas of highest need

A:- In Khugiani district of Nangrahar province. .(Kaga Bazar, Hakim Abad, Khair Mena, Banda, Sara Qala, Khawaran, Murdar Dand, Chamtala)

1:- 750 families will have access to drinking water and hygiene training
2:- 200 families receive hygiene and water kits.

B:- In Surkhrod district of Nangrahar province. (Tatang, Banda Mirlamje, Bala Bagh Daryab, Bar Kako Khil, Koz Sultanpor, Fati Abad,Bagh Bani, Bar kakrak, koz kakrak, Bala Bagh and Bagrami villages)
1:- 800 families will have access to drinking water and hygiene training in Tatang Nawab Jabar and Banda Mire Alamjee villages
2:- 200 families will receive hygiene and water kits.
3:- 50 families will have sanitation facility (Latrine)</narrative>
  </description>
